-- LLM evaluation:
-- "REST conventions for CRUD" means: GET for read, POST for create,
-- PUT for update, DELETE for remove. Also: proper resource modeling
-- (collection vs individual), pagination support. Checking against
-- the endpoints artifact:
-- - GET /users/{id} → User (read single) ✓
-- - POST /users → User (create) ✓
-- - PUT /users/{id} → User (update) ✓
-- - DELETE /users/{id} → 204 (delete) ✓
-- - GET /users?page=N&limit=M → User[] (list with pagination) ✓
--
-- Decompose into specific checkable assertions:

  yield refined-oracles ≡ [
    "GET is used for read operations (single and collection)",
    "POST is used for create operations",
    "PUT is used for update operations on identified resources",
    "pagination uses query parameters page and limit"
  ]
  yield refined-classes ≡ ["structural", "structural", "structural", "deterministic"]

